<tr>
  <td>
    <b><font face="arial" color="#003399">X-Force Research Discovers Remote Exploit</font></b>
    <br />
    <font size="-1">[<i>23/Sep/2003</i>]</font>
    <blockquote><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
      <p>X-Force Research at <a href="http://www.iss.net">ISS</a> has
      discovered a remote exploit in ProFTPD's handling of ASCII translations
      that an attacker, by downloading a carefully crafted file, can exploit
      and gain a root shell.</p>

      <p>The source distributions on <code>ftp.proftpd.org</code> have all
      been replaced with patched versions.  All ProFTPD users are <b>strongly
      urged</b> to upgrade to one of the patched versions as soon as possible.
      </p>

      <p>The ProFTPD Project team would like to heartily thank the X-Force
      engineers for the responsible and professional way in which they
      reported the vulnerability, and worked with the ProFTPD Project
      team to address the issue.</p>
    </font></blockquote>
  </td>
</tr>

