<tr>
  <td>
    <b><font face="arial" color="#003399">1.2.9rc1 released</font></b>
    <br />
    <font size="-1">[<i>16/May/2003</i>]</font>
    <blockquote><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
      <p>The ProFTPD team invites everyone to put their code testing
      hats on and give our latest release a try.  This testing release
      includes numerous bugfixes and new features, including:
      </p>
	  </font></blockquote>

	<blockquote>
	<b><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">New & Enhanced configuration directives</font></b>
	<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
	<dl>
	<dt>AnonRejectPasswords
	<dd>Configure a regular expression filter for commonly used anonymous login "passwords".
	<dt>RootRevoke
	<dt>Drop root privileges completely after authentication.  Safer, but disables some features (such as UserOwner).
	<dd>SocketOptions
	<dt>Combine existing directives for configuring TCP settings into a single directive, and add support for configuring the TCP maximum segment size.
	<dd>ListOptions</dd>
	<dt>ListOptions now supports optional parameters that can be used to set limits on recursive directory listings: "maxdepth", for
	limiting the maximum directory depth; "maxdirs", for limiting the maximum number of directories than will be listed; and
	"maxfiles", for limiting the maximum number of files that will be listed.</dt>
	</dl>
	</font>
	</blockquote>

	<blockquote>
	<b><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">New and Enhanced modules</font></b>
	<br><br>
	<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
	mod_ifsession, mod_radius, mod_rewrite, mod_tls
	</font>
	</blockquote>

	<blockquote>
	<b><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">Important Notes</font></b>
	<br><br>
	<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
	If you run proftpd with a ServerType of inetd, please make sure that all FTP sessions are ended, and that the current scoreboard is
	deleted, before installing and running proftpd-1.2.9rc1.  This is made necessary by scoreboard format changes in 1.2.9rc1.  Sites
	that run proftpd with a ServerType of standalone will be unaffected.
	</font></blockquote>

	<blockquote><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="-1">
	The new SocketOptions directive replaces and deprecates the following
	directives: tcpReceiveWindow, and tcpSendWindow.  Configurations that
	use these deprecated directives will need to be modified for use
	by proftpd-1.2.9rc1.
	</font></blockquote>
  </td>
